{"word":"H8041 - שָׂמַאל - sâmaʼl - saw-mal' - Left","slug":"H8041","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">שָׂמַאל</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>sâmaʼl"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>saw-mal'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Left"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E9;&#x05C2;&#x05DE;&#x05D0;&#x05DC; - s&#x0301;a&#x0302;ma'l</b> - <i>saw-mal'</i><p/>A primitive root (rather denominative from <a href=\"#/H8040\">H8040</a>); to use the <i>left</i> hand or pass in that direction: - (go, turn) (on the, to the) left."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H8040\">H8040</a>, <a href=\"#/H8042\">H8042</a>"}]}